WEBVTT

00:23.719 --> 00:29.072
♪ Can I take your hand?

00:29.116 --> 00:34.556
<i>♪ Do you understand?</i>

00:34.599 --> 00:39.648
<i>♪ You found my heart broken</i>

00:39.691 --> 00:45.871
<i>♪ And you helped me
make it whole ♪</i>

00:45.915 --> 00:51.442
♪ I'm starting to feel

00:51.486 --> 00:56.882
<i>♪ I found something real</i>

00:56.926 --> 01:01.974
<i>♪ The thought
of you fills me ♪</i>

01:02.018 --> 01:07.067
<i>♪ With a warmth
I've never known ♪</i>

01:07.110 --> 01:08.807
<i>♪</i>

01:08.851 --> 01:11.201
<i>♪ Hold</i>

01:11.245 --> 01:13.073
<i>♪ My heart...</i>

01:13.116 --> 01:15.988
- Floyd, I need you.

01:16.032 --> 01:18.861
Floyd, you're not still asleep
up there, are you?

01:18.904 --> 01:21.298
<i>- ♪ Hold</i>

01:21.342 --> 01:22.908
<i>♪ Mm</i>

01:22.952 --> 01:24.997
<i>♪ My heart</i>

01:25.041 --> 01:28.088
<i>♪ Till it grows</i>

01:28.131 --> 01:31.047
<i>♪ Old</i>

01:31.091 --> 01:36.139
<i>♪ Our love stays the same</i>

01:36.183 --> 01:40.839
<i>♪ Through time's
endless change ♪</i>

01:40.883 --> 01:44.365
<i>♪ Ooh, I promise</i>

01:44.408 --> 01:47.063
<i>♪ From now till death</i>

01:47.107 --> 01:53.069
<i>♪ You'll never be alone</i>

01:53.113 --> 01:54.592
<i>♪ Hold</i>

01:56.594 --> 02:02.296
<i>♪ My heart
till it grows old ♪</i>

02:02.339 --> 02:04.472
<i>♪ Ooh</i>

02:04.515 --> 02:07.388
<i>♪ Say you'll</i>

02:07.431 --> 02:10.347
<i>♪ Love me</i>

02:10.391 --> 02:15.265
<i>♪ Say you'll hold me</i>

02:15.309 --> 02:18.138
<i>♪ Through the stormy weather</i>

02:18.181 --> 02:20.836
<i>♪ We'll be together</i>

02:20.879 --> 02:27.059
<i>♪ Always</i>

02:27.103 --> 02:30.019
<i>♪ Say
you ♪</i>

02:30.062 --> 02:32.369
<i>♪ Love me</i>

02:32.413 --> 02:35.198
<i>♪ Say</i>

02:35.242 --> 02:40.421
<i>♪ You'll hold me
through the stormy weather ♪</i>

02:40.464 --> 02:43.163
<i>♪ We'll be together</i>

02:43.206 --> 02:48.603
<i>♪ Always</i>

02:48.646 --> 02:54.522
♪ Always

02:54.565 --> 02:57.655
<i>♪ Hold, ooh</i>

02:57.699 --> 03:03.748
<i>♪ My heart
till it grows old ♪</i>

03:03.792 --> 03:07.143
<i>♪ Ooh,
hold ♪</i>

03:07.187 --> 03:09.363
- Mm.

03:11.234 --> 03:14.150
I could stay here forever.

03:14.194 --> 03:16.457
- I am very open to that idea.

03:18.285 --> 03:20.896
- This is all I need.

03:30.775 --> 03:32.386
Oh, I have to...

03:32.429 --> 03:34.431
- Yeah, absolutely.

03:40.568 --> 03:43.832
<i>-</i>

03:50.273 --> 03:53.145
<i>-</i>

03:53.189 --> 03:56.323
- Um...

03:56.366 --> 03:59.413
<i>-</i>

04:02.459 --> 04:06.550
<i>-</i>

04:08.770 --> 04:11.990
<i>♪</i>

04:12.034 --> 04:13.688
- Everything okay?

04:16.865 --> 04:18.606
- Family stuff.

04:21.304 --> 04:26.570
<i>♪</i>

04:26.614 --> 04:28.093
- You wanted to see me, sir?
- Whoa, prompt.

04:28.137 --> 04:29.443
Good, I like that.

04:29.486 --> 04:31.140
Already demonstrating you've
got what it takes.

04:31.183 --> 04:32.359
- To do what, exactly?

04:32.402 --> 04:33.925
- To take over Dr. Kapoor's
department.

04:33.969 --> 04:37.712
Dr. Agnes Kao, interim chair
of neurology.

04:37.755 --> 04:39.191
Sorry, I like to keep things
on the move.

04:39.235 --> 04:40.410
We'll work on that.

04:40.454 --> 04:42.412
- I can't take over
Dr. Kapoor's department.

04:42.456 --> 04:43.457
- Why not?

04:43.500 --> 04:45.023
- I just finished
my fellowship.

04:45.067 --> 04:46.329
I just took the boards.

04:46.373 --> 04:48.549
- So how'd you do?
- 99th percentile, but--

04:48.592 --> 04:50.115
- You're gonna be great.
- But--

04:50.159 --> 04:54.163
- Behold, the king of cardiac,
the duke of hearts

04:54.206 --> 04:56.034
returns to New Amsterdam.
- Stop.

04:56.078 --> 04:57.253
- Sorry, it's too much?

04:57.297 --> 04:58.863
- Excuse me.
I'm sorry.

04:58.907 --> 05:01.170
You need to find someone else
until Dr. Kapoor comes back.

05:01.213 --> 05:02.693
Someone qualified.

05:02.737 --> 05:04.608
- You know, I'm trying to give
her her own department,

05:04.652 --> 05:06.218
and she's playing hardball.
- Been there.

05:06.262 --> 05:07.524
- What if I were just

05:07.568 --> 05:09.787
the interim-interim chair
of neurology?

05:09.831 --> 05:11.876
- Would that make you
more comfortable?

05:11.920 --> 05:12.921
- Only marginally.

05:12.964 --> 05:14.139
- Sold. You got it.

05:14.183 --> 05:16.316
Now get out there,
and go get 'em, tiger.

05:18.056 --> 05:19.623
- Yeah, how you holding up?

05:19.667 --> 05:22.147
- Well, I'll take the fifth on
that, but at least I'm here.

05:22.191 --> 05:24.367
- Well, I would love to be here
to witness

05:24.411 --> 05:25.934
your triumphant return.
- But?

05:25.977 --> 05:27.109
- I'm off to Connecticut.

05:27.152 --> 05:28.937
Assuming I survive rush hour
on the FDR

05:28.980 --> 05:31.635
and awkward silences with
Georgia's parents,

05:31.679 --> 05:34.116
I'm finally bringing home Luna.

05:34.159 --> 05:35.770
I can't wait to see the look
on her face

05:35.813 --> 05:37.554
when she sees me again.
- That's great, Max.

05:37.598 --> 05:39.121
What should I--
- Oh.

05:39.164 --> 05:42.690
Uh, see Helen for instructions
on your royal return.

05:42.733 --> 05:44.169
- Got it.

05:44.213 --> 05:45.519
- So, um...
where is he?

05:45.562 --> 05:47.434
- He's out there.

05:47.477 --> 05:48.739
- Got it, okay.

05:48.783 --> 05:50.132
- Good luck.
- Thank you.

05:53.222 --> 05:55.093
Linus Wilding?

05:55.137 --> 05:56.486
You Linus?

05:56.530 --> 05:58.619
Hi, how you doing?
I'm Dr. Frome.

05:58.662 --> 06:00.447
You can just call me Iggy.

06:00.490 --> 06:02.318
- I didn't do anything wrong.

06:02.362 --> 06:03.667
- No, I know.
I know that, I know.

06:03.711 --> 06:05.713
I'm just here to talk.
That's all.

06:05.756 --> 06:07.497
So, burning question.

06:07.541 --> 06:08.933
You ever run away before?

06:10.413 --> 06:12.197
No?
You ever wanted to?

06:14.461 --> 06:16.114
Okay.

06:16.158 --> 06:18.508
So then I got to assume that
something big,

06:18.552 --> 06:19.727
something major happened,
right?

06:19.770 --> 06:21.772
To make you want to do it now.

06:21.816 --> 06:24.514
And I know that this is hard to
talk about,

06:24.558 --> 06:27.387
but I have to ask...

06:27.430 --> 06:28.779
did somebody hurt you,
physically?

06:28.823 --> 06:31.478
- I didn't run away, okay?

06:31.521 --> 06:33.436
My mom, she...

06:33.480 --> 06:34.959
she threw me out.

06:36.352 --> 06:38.049
- Okay.

06:38.093 --> 06:40.617
Well, maybe you can help me
understand this, then.

06:42.271 --> 06:45.405
Why did she call the police and
file a missing persons report?

06:45.448 --> 06:49.757
<i>♪</i>

06:51.149 --> 06:52.760
Okay.
Hi.

06:56.067 --> 06:58.287
- I'm so grateful you found
him, Dr. Frome.

06:58.330 --> 07:00.855
I haven't slept in days.
- Yeah, I can only imagine.

07:00.898 --> 07:02.204
Um...

07:02.247 --> 07:03.466
did you manage to bring
the things I--

07:03.510 --> 07:04.902
- Yes, everything
you asked for.

07:04.946 --> 07:07.296
Linus's birth certificate,
immunization forms,

07:07.339 --> 07:08.819
and recent school ID.

07:08.863 --> 07:10.821
- Oh, great, thank you.

07:10.865 --> 07:12.736
Okay.

07:12.780 --> 07:14.825
Ms. Wilding, can you think
of any reason why

07:14.869 --> 07:18.438
there's confusion about the
events that led Linus to leave?

07:18.481 --> 07:19.482
Did you guys have a fight?
Anything?

07:19.526 --> 07:20.788
- No.

07:20.831 --> 07:22.790
Four weeks ago,
I sent him off to camp,

07:22.833 --> 07:24.182
and he never came home.

07:27.142 --> 07:28.448
- Okay.

07:30.928 --> 07:32.582
Okay.

07:32.626 --> 07:34.410
Okay, here's what I think

07:34.454 --> 07:35.890
The three of us should
have a chat,

07:35.933 --> 07:37.718
maybe clear up any of this
confusion that's going on.

07:37.761 --> 07:39.067
- Absolutely.
- Okay.

07:39.110 --> 07:40.329
I think now would be
a good time.

07:40.372 --> 07:41.461
Are you okay with that?

07:44.551 --> 07:45.639
Linus.

07:53.777 --> 07:55.083
- What's going on here?

07:56.301 --> 07:58.521
- Well, I think your son
is feeling a little--

07:58.565 --> 08:01.176
- I don't know who that is, but
that is definitely not my son.

08:04.614 --> 08:06.964
- I'm--

08:07.008 --> 08:08.705
I'm fairly confident that is.

08:08.749 --> 08:10.359
- He looks like my son,
Dr. Frome, I know.

08:10.402 --> 08:12.796
But they are not the same.

08:12.840 --> 08:14.537
No, that boy is an imposter.

08:16.191 --> 08:18.976
- A mother knows.
A mother can tell.

08:20.543 --> 08:21.675
That's not my son.

08:25.069 --> 08:29.683
<i>♪</i>

08:34.949 --> 08:37.560
- There he is, in the flesh.
- Good to see you, Max.

08:37.604 --> 08:39.519
- No place I'd rather be.
-

08:40.650 --> 08:41.825
- Hey. Calvin.

08:41.869 --> 08:44.654
- I hope your drive wasn't
too bad.

08:44.698 --> 08:46.134
- Yeah, it was okay.

08:46.177 --> 08:48.179
- We've got Luna's stuff all
packed up, ready to go.

08:48.223 --> 08:51.269
- Oh, that's very sweet.
Thank you, thank you, Gwen.

08:51.313 --> 08:52.532
Where is she hiding?

08:52.575 --> 08:54.316
- Oh, she's just
in the living room, playing.

08:54.359 --> 08:55.709
- Oh, great.

08:55.752 --> 08:57.972
- Please say you'll stay
for lunch.

08:58.015 --> 09:00.104
I'm perfecting
my bread machine.

09:00.148 --> 09:02.803
- No, I couldn't--
couldn't say no to that.

09:02.846 --> 09:05.414
Of course.
I, um...

09:05.457 --> 09:06.850
I would love that.

09:06.894 --> 09:09.897
- All this one-on-one time
with her was priceless.

09:09.940 --> 09:12.856
Luna!
Guess who's here.

09:16.904 --> 09:18.949
- Luna!
Dada's here.

09:31.571 --> 09:38.229
<i>♪</i>

09:38.273 --> 09:41.406
- Hammond Sims, 25-year-old
male, possible kidney stones.

09:41.450 --> 09:42.582
- More like boulders.

09:42.625 --> 09:43.757
- You'll be all right, brother.

09:43.800 --> 09:45.323
- How long have you had
this pain for?

09:45.367 --> 09:46.498
- It's been a minute.

09:46.542 --> 09:48.022
Thought to come in
when it first hit...

09:49.414 --> 09:50.851
But the nightclub got wiped out
by the 'rona.

09:50.894 --> 09:52.113
No health insurance.

09:52.156 --> 09:54.289
- Oh, yeah, you and half
the city.

09:56.073 --> 09:57.466
Oh, snap.

09:57.509 --> 09:59.207
- Okay, okay, we're gonna get
you dialed in--

09:59.250 --> 10:00.512
- Get away from me!

10:02.427 --> 10:04.212
- Stop!
No, stop!

10:07.519 --> 10:09.696
- Guy's on K2!
Call security!

10:12.220 --> 10:13.656
Ahh!
- Casey!

10:13.700 --> 10:15.527
- I will kill you!

10:17.921 --> 10:21.272
I see you!
I see you all!

10:24.319 --> 10:26.800
<i>♪</i>

10:26.843 --> 10:28.715
I see you all!

10:34.764 --> 10:36.331
- Brunstetter's in surgery.

10:36.374 --> 10:38.246
Fractured ocular orbit.

10:38.289 --> 10:39.726
- That guy just snapped.

10:39.769 --> 10:41.858
- I knew he was on something
when we admitted him.

10:41.902 --> 10:43.817
I should've paged security
right then.

10:43.860 --> 10:45.166
- No, it's on me.

10:45.209 --> 10:47.516
I should've gotten there
faster or been closer--

10:47.559 --> 10:48.430
- Hey.

10:48.473 --> 10:50.084
This is not your fault.

10:50.127 --> 10:52.303
Or yours or yours.

10:52.347 --> 10:54.741
How many of us have been
attacked while on the job?

10:56.699 --> 10:58.527
Assaulted...

10:58.570 --> 11:01.008
slapped, bit, kicked, clawed.

11:01.051 --> 11:02.487
Come on.

11:04.664 --> 11:06.622
How many of you feel unsafe
working here?

11:09.538 --> 11:12.019
- They said they were gonna
install metal detectors.

11:12.062 --> 11:13.585
- I heard
more security cameras.

11:13.629 --> 11:15.805
- Yeah, we keep waiting for
someone else to protect us.

11:15.849 --> 11:18.460
And now one of our own.

11:18.503 --> 11:20.462
We all deserve to feel safe.

11:20.505 --> 11:22.464
And today, I am gonna
make that happen.

11:22.507 --> 11:23.770
- Incoming!
- Oh, got another one.

11:23.813 --> 11:24.901
-Here we go.

11:26.816 --> 11:29.819
- No, no,
flight 117 isn't gonna work

11:29.863 --> 11:31.865
because I need to leave New York now

11:31.908 --> 11:33.214
to get there in time.

11:35.433 --> 11:37.566
Yes, I appreciate
it's short notice, ma'am,

11:37.609 --> 11:38.828
but that's partly due
to the fact

11:38.872 --> 11:41.135
that I waited 45 minutes
to talk to you.

11:43.485 --> 11:45.574
- I'm back and reporting
for duty.

11:45.617 --> 11:49.404
- Yeah, yes, I'll gladly hold
one more time.

11:49.447 --> 11:53.451
Wait, you're back...
like, here?

11:53.495 --> 11:55.802
- Max didn't tell you
I was starting today?

11:55.845 --> 11:57.107
- No,

11:57.151 --> 11:59.544
which is odd,
because he's usually so great

11:59.588 --> 12:01.329
about communicating
important information.

12:01.372 --> 12:02.939
Did he say
what I was supposed to do?

12:02.983 --> 12:06.900
- He said you have instructions
for my royal re...

12:06.943 --> 12:08.815
Why don't I just pop
up to cardio and jump in

12:08.858 --> 12:09.641
where they need me?

12:09.685 --> 12:12.166
- Sounds great, thank you.

12:12.209 --> 12:13.776
- Is everything good with you?

12:13.820 --> 12:16.170
- I'm just trying to book
a last-minute flight to Iran,

12:16.213 --> 12:17.562
but no one's willing to help,
so--

12:17.606 --> 12:18.781
- Iran?

12:18.825 --> 12:21.392
- It's my brother.

12:22.219 --> 12:26.093
Yes, n--
yes, I'm here.

12:26.136 --> 12:28.095
No. No, no, no, no, no, no.

12:28.138 --> 12:32.577
A layover isn't going to work
because it's time sensitive.

12:32.621 --> 12:34.797
Sorry, can I speak to
your supervisor, please?

12:34.841 --> 12:38.453
- God, she's so big.
-

12:38.496 --> 12:40.847
- And she uses a fork.
She's like a real person.

12:40.890 --> 12:42.849
- When you see the floor
after she's done,

12:42.892 --> 12:44.981
it won't seem as impressive.
-

12:45.025 --> 12:46.156
What about peas?

12:46.200 --> 12:47.941
She used to love peas
for lunch.

12:47.984 --> 12:50.378
Dada misses seeing you chomp
on those peas...

12:50.421 --> 12:52.293
- Mm.

12:52.336 --> 12:53.947
- Yeah...
- What?

12:53.990 --> 12:57.385
- Luna's perhaps not as much of
a pea aficionado these days.

12:57.428 --> 13:00.388
- No, she hates them.
Truly.

13:00.431 --> 13:03.304
- Really?
That's new.

13:07.047 --> 13:10.267
- Anyway, what she really loves
is sausage.

13:10.311 --> 13:12.661
- Sausage? No.
- Yeah.

13:12.704 --> 13:15.446
Gwen, show him the thing.
- Yeah.

13:15.490 --> 13:19.886
♪ Sausage, sausage,
sausage, sa... ♪

13:21.148 --> 13:24.107
- ♪ Sausage, sausage, boop!
Boo-do-do ♪

13:24.151 --> 13:28.111
Wow!
-

13:29.112 --> 13:33.638
<i>♪</i>

13:41.211 --> 13:42.343
- There's nothing wrong
with me.

13:42.386 --> 13:43.823
I feel fine.

13:43.866 --> 13:47.087
- I know you do, but I'd like
to run some tests, okay?

13:47.130 --> 13:48.653
- You don't understand.

13:48.697 --> 13:51.656
He was supposed to come home
from camp, and he never did.

13:52.962 --> 13:54.529
Doesn't make any sense.

13:54.572 --> 13:56.618
<i>And then that other kid
just shows up,</i>

13:56.661 --> 13:58.794
<i>claiming to be my son.</i>

13:58.838 --> 14:02.537
- Yana, I need you to take
a deep breath and hold it.

14:11.285 --> 14:12.895
And exhale.

14:12.939 --> 14:14.941
<i>- Doing great, Yana.
Good job.</i>

14:16.333 --> 14:18.031
- So scary.

14:19.902 --> 14:25.212
This random person trying to
convince me he's my son.

14:25.255 --> 14:26.866
Pretending.

14:28.519 --> 14:30.521
- You're sure they're related?

14:30.565 --> 14:32.436
- Yes, I'm sure.
I checked.

14:32.480 --> 14:34.482
Linus is definitely her son.

14:34.525 --> 14:36.701
There's gotta be
a better explanation.

14:39.269 --> 14:40.444
- There is.

14:43.447 --> 14:46.581
<i>♪</i>

14:46.624 --> 14:49.671
- So, you won't believe how
fast HCC works

14:49.714 --> 14:50.977
when you threaten
to call the media.

14:51.020 --> 14:52.761
- We're getting new
security cameras.

14:52.804 --> 14:55.546
- Better. They finally agreed
to cough up some cash

14:55.590 --> 14:58.506
for actual security
around here.

14:58.549 --> 14:59.986
-
Excuse me.

15:00.029 --> 15:01.248
Is there a Dr. Bloom?

15:01.291 --> 15:02.510
- Ta-da.

15:02.553 --> 15:04.033
Yes, officers.
Welcome.

15:04.077 --> 15:07.384
Thinking we would plant
you here, there,

15:07.428 --> 15:09.604
and how 'bout over there?

15:12.215 --> 15:15.044
Private hospitals have had cops
in the ED for years.

15:15.088 --> 15:16.524
About time we got our own.

15:16.567 --> 15:18.743
Problem solved.

15:24.619 --> 15:27.622
<i>♪</i>

15:33.628 --> 15:34.890
Put me in, coach.

15:34.934 --> 15:36.065
- Floyd, hey!
So great to see you.

15:36.109 --> 15:37.588
We just heard you were
coming back.

15:39.068 --> 15:41.853
- Just heard, like...
- Ten minutes ago?

15:41.897 --> 15:43.507
- Hm.
Should've seen that coming.

15:43.551 --> 15:46.032
- Max isn't great
with communication.

15:46.075 --> 15:48.208
- Yeah, so I hear.
Well, sorry to surprise you,

15:48.251 --> 15:51.515
but I am back, I'm here,
I'm ready for action, and, uh,

15:51.559 --> 15:53.082
yeah, just put me wherever
you want.

15:53.126 --> 15:54.388
I'll do
that triple valve replacement.

15:54.431 --> 15:56.390
- Oh, Alvarez is already
on that one.

15:56.433 --> 15:57.478
- Oh, okay, well.

15:57.521 --> 15:59.523
Can't expect to start
at the top.

15:59.567 --> 16:02.657
What about the aortic valve
replacement in OR 2?

16:02.700 --> 16:04.180
That's you.

16:04.224 --> 16:06.182
-
It's been crazy around here.

16:06.226 --> 16:08.010
COVID cut
our elective surgeries in half.

16:08.054 --> 16:11.579
- Wow, okay.
Um, hell, I'll do anything.

16:11.622 --> 16:13.407
What about the
mediastinal node biopsy?

16:13.450 --> 16:15.583
- Okay, I know how
this looks...

16:17.585 --> 16:19.195
- Duke, wow.

16:19.239 --> 16:20.980
Well, Duke,
he's still a resident.

16:21.023 --> 16:23.547
I could supervise.
- Already assigned.

16:23.591 --> 16:25.158
- Wow.

16:26.289 --> 16:28.596
- Hey, go set up your office,

16:28.639 --> 16:30.467
and I'll page you
if something comes up.

16:30.511 --> 16:33.079
- I don't really have
an office.

16:36.082 --> 16:37.909
- No, it's on reserve.

16:37.953 --> 16:40.173
They're just waiting
on the visa.

16:40.216 --> 16:41.652
Well, couldn't you...

16:41.696 --> 16:46.005
Y--okay, yes, I understand.

16:46.048 --> 16:48.442
Yeah.
Yes, I'll have my phone on.

16:50.531 --> 16:52.359
- Hey.

16:52.402 --> 16:54.056
Just wanted to check in on you

16:54.100 --> 16:55.797
after that phone call
this morning.

16:55.840 --> 16:56.972
- It's fine.

16:58.104 --> 17:00.106
- I didn't know you spoke
Farsi.

17:00.149 --> 17:01.455
- Well, I do.

17:03.283 --> 17:05.763
- I don't know what's going on,
but I'm here.

17:05.807 --> 17:06.982
Let me help.

17:08.505 --> 17:11.421
- I need an immigration lawyer,
not a trauma surgeon.

17:12.553 --> 17:14.729
- Well, I definitely didn't
come here to make things worse.

17:14.772 --> 17:17.601
- I've spent this day wrangling
travel agents and visas,

17:17.645 --> 17:19.821
and it's been nothing short
of a bureaucratic nightmare.

17:19.864 --> 17:22.519
I'm barely holding it together.

17:22.563 --> 17:26.088
So I'm sorry, but I really
don't want to talk about it...

17:29.135 --> 17:31.093
<i>♪</i>

17:31.137 --> 17:32.529
With anyone.

17:36.446 --> 17:38.100
- Best immigration lawyer
in Manhattan.

17:40.885 --> 17:44.280
<i>♪</i>

17:44.324 --> 17:48.502
- "The dear deer dart
and play,

17:48.545 --> 17:50.982
while the crow crows
the night away."

17:51.026 --> 17:52.201
- Sorry to interrupt.

17:52.245 --> 17:53.942
Cal, do you think you could
help get her

17:53.985 --> 17:55.161
in the car real quick with me?

17:59.861 --> 18:01.515
Come on, Luna.

18:01.558 --> 18:03.299
We're gonna see Grampy
and Grammy real soon.

18:05.388 --> 18:07.086
- I mean, maybe stay
another few minutes.

18:07.129 --> 18:08.522
I think she just needs a nap.

18:08.565 --> 18:09.653
- Yeah, I know.

18:09.697 --> 18:10.828
I just think
I need to get her home.

18:10.872 --> 18:13.396
- Okay.
All righty.

18:15.833 --> 18:17.444
Oof.

18:17.487 --> 18:18.880
- All right.
Thank you, Cal.

18:18.923 --> 18:21.012
- No go.
No go!

18:21.056 --> 18:22.840
Mama here.

18:25.887 --> 18:32.763
<i>♪</i>

18:34.200 --> 18:37.812
- We found small lesions
in your mother's brain.

18:37.855 --> 18:41.163
And they are the reason why
she has been so confused.

18:43.122 --> 18:44.732
- Okay.

18:45.428 --> 18:48.170
- It's a rare
misidentification disorder

18:48.214 --> 18:50.390
known as Capgras syndrome.

18:54.089 --> 18:56.787
- But what does that even mean?

18:56.831 --> 19:00.878
- Well, it's like her brain's
facial recognition system

19:00.922 --> 19:03.272
has been rewired.

19:03.316 --> 19:05.274
And the emotional ties
that she should feel

19:05.318 --> 19:08.886
when she looks at you are lost.

19:08.930 --> 19:10.149
She doesn't feel them.

19:12.412 --> 19:15.415
- She thinks
you're an imposter.

19:17.025 --> 19:18.635
- But--but I'm not.

19:18.679 --> 19:20.115
I mean, I'm me.

19:20.159 --> 19:23.118
She was fine when I went
to camp, and...

19:24.772 --> 19:28.428
I don't understand
what's happening.

19:28.471 --> 19:30.560
- If the lesions were
in a different spot,

19:30.604 --> 19:33.259
maybe we could do surgery,
but in your mother's case,

19:33.302 --> 19:34.869
it's not an option.

19:36.958 --> 19:41.615
- Well, there's gotta be some
medicine she can take, right?

19:41.658 --> 19:44.531
- Yeah, I've already
prescribed it,

19:44.574 --> 19:48.187
but the meds will only stop her
symptoms from getting worse.

19:49.666 --> 19:50.798
Uh...

19:50.841 --> 19:55.585
Linus, there's no easy way
to say this.

19:55.629 --> 19:58.501
Your mother is never going
to recognize you again.

20:01.287 --> 20:04.420
Her condition is permanent.

20:04.464 --> 20:07.597
- So she's never
gonna know who I am?

20:10.774 --> 20:12.907
<i>♪</i>

20:12.950 --> 20:14.169
- I am so sorry.

20:14.213 --> 20:16.867
- But--but she's my mom.

20:16.911 --> 20:20.262
I mean, I don't have
anyone else who...

20:20.306 --> 20:23.091
well, what am I supposed to do?
Where--

20:23.134 --> 20:25.267
Where will I go?
She's my mom.

20:25.311 --> 20:32.274
<i>♪</i>

20:36.887 --> 20:39.281
- Okay.

20:39.325 --> 20:41.979
Where are we on the pain scale
now, big guy?

20:44.286 --> 20:45.983
Seven.

20:46.027 --> 20:47.463
- That's better.

20:47.507 --> 20:48.899
- Zero would be better.

20:48.943 --> 20:51.337
- Let's up his morphine
2 milligrams.

20:53.817 --> 20:56.037
These kidney stones
ain't no joke.

20:56.080 --> 20:58.431
- Don't worry, it'll pass.

20:58.474 --> 21:00.694
Get it?
"Pass."

21:02.652 --> 21:04.915
Come on.
It's funny because it's true.

21:06.482 --> 21:09.180
What? Nothing?
Wow.

21:09.224 --> 21:11.008
Tough crowd.

21:11.052 --> 21:12.271
- Can we talk?

21:18.886 --> 21:19.974
- What's going on?

21:23.194 --> 21:24.544
- It's the cops.

21:24.587 --> 21:27.286
- But they're here for us.

21:27.329 --> 21:28.852
To keep us safe.

21:32.552 --> 21:34.771
- You know what I see?

21:34.815 --> 21:37.470
I see the people
who've been stopping me

21:37.513 --> 21:38.819
since I was 12 years old,

21:38.862 --> 21:41.038
making me sit on curbs
and face walls.

21:41.082 --> 21:44.215
I got handcuffed coming home
from work one day in my scrubs.

21:44.259 --> 21:45.521
In my scrubs.

21:45.565 --> 21:47.784
- Casey, come on.
You know that I would never--

21:47.828 --> 21:49.786
- Ask Weber and ask Mariana,
Lauren.

21:49.830 --> 21:51.310
We all got stories.

21:51.353 --> 21:52.659
Hell, why don't you ask
your little friend

21:52.702 --> 21:54.574
who's always up in here
using our showers?

21:54.617 --> 21:55.879
Yeah.

21:55.923 --> 21:57.359
I noticed.

21:57.403 --> 21:59.187
Ask her if she feels
any safer

21:59.230 --> 22:00.362
with all these cops
hanging around

22:00.406 --> 22:01.494
watching everything she does.

22:01.537 --> 22:02.843
- Okay. Right.

22:02.886 --> 22:05.236
So what are we supposed
to do next time

22:05.280 --> 22:07.151
there's another assault, huh?

22:07.195 --> 22:08.675
Brunstetter's still upstairs

22:08.718 --> 22:10.329
getting his eye socket
repaired.

22:10.372 --> 22:11.678
You think he'd want
them gone?

22:11.721 --> 22:13.375
- You think cops make
trans people feel safe?

22:13.419 --> 22:15.377
- Casey, I'm not blind, okay?

22:15.421 --> 22:17.074
I know that there
are bad cops--

22:17.118 --> 22:19.250
- You didn't just try to "not
all cops" me now, did you?

22:19.294 --> 22:21.252
- But it's not all cops.

22:21.296 --> 22:22.384
And you know that.

22:22.428 --> 22:24.386
And we need them here.
- "We"?

22:24.430 --> 22:26.083
Tell me who's "we."

22:26.127 --> 22:28.564
Because the undocumented,
they're gonna stay away.

22:28.608 --> 22:30.914
The homeless,
they're gonna stay away, too.

22:30.958 --> 22:32.829
And what about the next patient
who comes in here

22:32.873 --> 22:34.135
under the influence?

22:34.178 --> 22:36.050
You suddenly want these cops
feeling compelled

22:36.093 --> 22:38.095
to make arrests because, hell,
they're already here?

22:38.139 --> 22:40.489
What could possibly go wrong?

22:43.971 --> 22:49.672
<i>♪</i>

22:51.805 --> 22:54.982
They're not making us feel
any safer, Lauren.

22:55.025 --> 22:57.463
It's just a different kind
of unsafe.

23:13.783 --> 23:20.355
<i>♪</i>

23:51.821 --> 23:56.826
<i>♪</i>

23:56.870 --> 23:59.002
- Got a diaphragmatic repair.

23:59.046 --> 24:00.830
- 40-year-old model rocket
enthusiast

24:00.874 --> 24:02.179
ironically failed to launch.

24:02.223 --> 24:04.486
I'll need an OR.
Oh, and another set of hands.

24:04.530 --> 24:06.575
- Right in here,
but we're short staffed.

24:06.619 --> 24:08.055
- I'm available.

24:08.098 --> 24:09.143
- Who are you?

24:09.186 --> 24:10.797
- Floyd Reynolds,
cardiothoracic.

24:10.840 --> 24:12.538
- Ever worked
a diaphragm before?

24:12.581 --> 24:14.148
- Once or twice.

24:17.107 --> 24:21.024
<i>♪</i>

24:21.068 --> 24:24.941
- And we have liftoff.

24:24.985 --> 24:26.203
Diaphragm is exposed.

24:26.247 --> 24:28.510
- Oof, rocket did some damage.

24:28.554 --> 24:30.556
- Yeah,
one small step for mankind,

24:30.599 --> 24:33.341
one huge abdominal tear
for James Feller.

24:33.384 --> 24:34.995
Biological mesh.

24:35.038 --> 24:37.040
- You know, a monofilament
mattress suture

24:37.084 --> 24:38.389
might work better.

24:38.433 --> 24:40.000
- Mesh will provide
a tension-free closure.

24:40.043 --> 24:41.392
- Yeah, but why not close it

24:41.436 --> 24:44.265
without introducing
a foreign object, you know?

24:44.308 --> 24:45.527
- Because the uneven edges

24:45.571 --> 24:47.747
of the monofilament closure
would pucker.

24:47.790 --> 24:50.184
- Eh, sutures could be laid
down to minimize it.

24:50.227 --> 24:52.229
- I'm sorry, Doctor...?
- Reynolds.

24:52.273 --> 24:53.840
- Dr. Reynolds was chair
of cardiothoracic--

24:53.883 --> 24:55.319
- Oh, it's fine, Kat.

24:55.363 --> 24:57.017
- Chair or no chair, I asked
for another set of hands,

24:57.060 --> 24:58.018
not a second opinion.

25:00.411 --> 25:02.109
This is my OR,
and surgeries will be done

25:02.152 --> 25:03.371
the way I want them.

25:03.414 --> 25:05.547
Now, you can either
get on board or get out.

25:08.637 --> 25:10.683
- On board it is.

25:10.726 --> 25:12.032
- Mesh.

25:12.075 --> 25:13.990
- No, it's above and beyond.
Truly.

25:14.034 --> 25:15.731
Thank you.

25:15.775 --> 25:17.080
Okay, you too.
Buh-bye.

25:19.474 --> 25:22.042
Okay, so Linus's cousin in Ohio

25:22.085 --> 25:23.870
is going to take him in
permanently.

25:23.913 --> 25:25.524
- That's good news, right?

25:25.567 --> 25:29.397
- It's better than foster care.
That's true.

25:29.440 --> 25:32.356
Or worse yet,
a runaway shelter.

25:34.750 --> 25:37.536
Oh, man.

25:37.579 --> 25:39.668
- So what's wrong?

25:39.712 --> 25:41.235
- It's Yana.

25:41.278 --> 25:42.410
I can't stop thinking
about Yana.

25:42.453 --> 25:43.890
I mean, she's still convinced

25:43.933 --> 25:46.414
that her son is out there
somewhere, right?

25:46.457 --> 25:47.894
And she's never gonna stop
looking for him,

25:47.937 --> 25:49.896
and we will never be able to
convince her of the truth.

25:49.939 --> 25:51.550
That's just facts.

25:51.593 --> 25:53.290
It's all just so...

25:59.514 --> 26:00.646
- What?

26:01.429 --> 26:02.735
- What?

26:02.778 --> 26:04.084
- You're looking at me.

26:04.127 --> 26:05.738
- Oh, yeah.

26:07.391 --> 26:08.610
Yeah, I think this is usually
the time

26:08.654 --> 26:10.133
when Vijay says
something profound

26:10.177 --> 26:12.571
and gives me like a...
a good idea.

26:12.614 --> 26:13.746
- Well, I don't know
what to say!

26:13.789 --> 26:14.964
- Just try something.
Throw it at me.

26:15.008 --> 26:16.183
- Try what?

26:16.226 --> 26:17.750
Yana thinks that Linus is
an imposter,

26:17.793 --> 26:19.621
and you'll never be able to
convince her that he isn't.

26:19.665 --> 26:21.014
- I just said that.

26:21.057 --> 26:22.450
- Just like you'll never be
able to convince me

26:22.493 --> 26:23.669
that I can fill
Dr. Kapoor's shoes.

26:23.712 --> 26:24.931
These are facts!

26:24.974 --> 26:26.106
I can't do this,

26:26.149 --> 26:28.021
and Linus may as well be dead.

26:28.064 --> 26:30.850
So no, I don't know
what to say.

26:30.893 --> 26:33.156
- That's...

26:33.200 --> 26:34.636
that's genius.

26:34.680 --> 26:36.333
- What is?

26:36.377 --> 26:37.683
- Therapeutic fibbing.

26:37.726 --> 26:39.772
That is a great success
in similar syndromes.

26:42.818 --> 26:44.124
- Wait, no.

26:44.167 --> 26:46.474
You want to tell her that
her son is dead?

26:46.517 --> 26:48.258
I didn't mean that literally.

26:48.302 --> 26:49.477
- Look, all she wants
is a way to move on.

26:49.520 --> 26:51.348
Right?
A way to get on with her life.

26:51.392 --> 26:53.524
- Oh, what about Linus?

26:53.568 --> 26:56.484
He lost his mom, and he knows
that she's not dead.

26:56.527 --> 26:58.399
- Yeah, he's looking
for a relationship with her.

26:58.442 --> 27:01.097
He's looking for a connection.
That's it, so...

27:01.141 --> 27:02.621
why don't we give him one?

27:07.190 --> 27:08.539
- One of you took it!

27:08.583 --> 27:10.672
- Hey.

27:10.716 --> 27:12.543
Thanks for getting rid
of those cops.

27:12.587 --> 27:14.502
- Yeah, yeah.
Back to covering our own butts.

27:14.545 --> 27:16.678
- Give it back!
- And right on cue.

27:16.722 --> 27:19.159
- It's my phone.
I know you took it!

27:19.202 --> 27:20.987
And I want it back.
- Sir, can you just...?

27:21.030 --> 27:22.336
- But sir--sir!

27:22.379 --> 27:23.685
You told us you left your phone
at the bar.

27:23.729 --> 27:25.121
- Not true.
- Everyone stay back.

27:25.165 --> 27:26.906
- Where's my phone?
- No, Casey, I mean it.

27:26.949 --> 27:28.995
If anyone else is getting hurt
today, it's gonna be me.

27:29.038 --> 27:30.170
- Think you can just
hold me here?

27:30.213 --> 27:31.606
- Sir, sir.
I need you to look at me.

27:31.650 --> 27:33.347
We're gonna get you
sobered up,

27:33.390 --> 27:34.696
and we're gonna get you
out of here.

27:34.740 --> 27:36.393
But right now, I need you
to return to your bed.

27:36.437 --> 27:38.265
- I do not need to sober up.

27:38.308 --> 27:40.354
What I need is my damn phone.

27:40.397 --> 27:42.051
- No, you need to return
to your bed.

27:42.095 --> 27:43.531
Can you do that for me?

27:43.574 --> 27:45.707
- I'm not getting back
in that stupid bed.

27:45.751 --> 27:46.839
And you can't make me.

27:46.882 --> 27:48.667
- This is my ED.

27:48.710 --> 27:50.103
I make the rules.

27:50.146 --> 27:53.236
Now put your damn mask on,
and get back in your bed!

27:58.285 --> 28:03.594
<i>♪</i>

28:13.604 --> 28:16.825
I bet this whole "I'm a tank"
thing you got going on

28:16.869 --> 28:19.785
comes in pretty handy when you
mess up someone's drink.

28:19.828 --> 28:22.831
- Actually, I was a bouncer.

28:22.875 --> 28:25.312
- Not sure how I missed that.

28:39.108 --> 28:40.719
- Thank you for the lawyer.

28:40.762 --> 28:42.329
- Did she help?

28:44.244 --> 28:45.636
- It was too late.

28:50.859 --> 28:52.731
My brother died.

28:56.212 --> 28:57.736
Half-brother.

29:00.608 --> 29:04.307
We weren't close,
but...

29:04.351 --> 29:07.397
I mean, I wanted to be,
I just...

29:07.441 --> 29:09.748
I just thought
that I had time.

29:12.141 --> 29:13.752
According to Islam,

29:13.795 --> 29:16.885
he needed to be buried
before the next sundown.

29:16.929 --> 29:18.757
But I ran out of time.

29:21.063 --> 29:24.023
I keep...

29:24.066 --> 29:25.807
I keep running out of time.

29:28.549 --> 29:33.380
And I--I nearly got there,
but then my visa...

29:34.990 --> 29:36.122
What does it matter?

29:36.165 --> 29:38.951
I don't want to make excuses
anymore.

29:38.994 --> 29:40.996
About him...

29:41.040 --> 29:42.824
about you.

29:50.701 --> 29:52.703
- What was your brother's name?

29:55.358 --> 29:58.100
-
Farhad.

30:01.147 --> 30:08.241
<i>♪</i>

30:13.028 --> 30:14.508
- Sorry.

30:14.551 --> 30:17.250
We haven't visited since...

30:19.861 --> 30:21.428
Since the funeral.

30:27.738 --> 30:30.132
She just thinks
we're at the park.

30:30.176 --> 30:33.179
She doesn't realize...

30:33.222 --> 30:34.876
"Mama here."

30:38.924 --> 30:40.926
I want to do the right thing,
but I...

30:40.969 --> 30:42.666
I don't know what that is.

30:48.281 --> 30:51.893
I love her so much.
I just don't know...

30:51.937 --> 30:54.940
if I'm enough...

30:54.983 --> 30:56.506
without you.

31:01.860 --> 31:06.255
I don't know if
I'm ever gonna be enough.

31:17.223 --> 31:18.180
- Hi.

31:18.224 --> 31:21.531
Just came by to check in.

31:21.575 --> 31:23.055
I know this has been a lot,

31:23.098 --> 31:25.753
with the diagnosis
and your son.

31:25.796 --> 31:27.233
- I can't believe he's gone.

31:29.931 --> 31:31.628
And the strangest thing is,

31:31.672 --> 31:34.544
a part of me feels...

31:34.588 --> 31:36.590
relieved

31:36.633 --> 31:38.287
to finally know the truth.

31:40.420 --> 31:43.292
Is that awful of me?

31:43.336 --> 31:44.772
- No.

31:44.815 --> 31:46.034
No.

31:46.078 --> 31:49.472
- When I thought
he was still out there,

31:49.516 --> 31:52.475
all alone, lost,

31:52.519 --> 31:55.739
needing me,
and I couldn't find him, it...

31:55.783 --> 31:59.352
it was excruciating.

31:59.395 --> 32:01.920
Now...

32:01.963 --> 32:03.791
- Now you can grieve.

32:07.229 --> 32:08.796
I get it.

32:11.886 --> 32:13.453
Yeah.

32:15.934 --> 32:17.239
So, listen,

32:17.283 --> 32:21.591
I know that this might not
be the best time, but...

32:21.635 --> 32:24.116
there's actually
someone here

32:24.159 --> 32:26.161
that is going through
the exact same thing,

32:26.205 --> 32:29.164
if you wanted to talk to him.

32:29.208 --> 32:31.471
- Now?

32:31.514 --> 32:33.125
- Yeah.

32:33.168 --> 32:35.301
I think that it would be great
for you to talk to someone

32:35.344 --> 32:38.173
who knows what this feels like.

32:38.217 --> 32:39.914
You know?

32:39.958 --> 32:42.482
But only if you want to.
It's up to you.

32:45.702 --> 32:47.356
Yeah?
Okay.

32:58.411 --> 33:01.109
- You!
- She doesn't want to see me.

33:01.153 --> 33:02.806
- No, no, no.
Yana, hang on, listen.

33:02.850 --> 33:04.547
Just hear him out, okay?

33:04.591 --> 33:06.114
- He broke into my house!

33:06.158 --> 33:08.160
- I know, I know, and that
must have been really scary.

33:08.203 --> 33:12.294
But I'm asking you if you would
please let him explain.

33:12.338 --> 33:13.513
That's all.

33:20.041 --> 33:22.348
Thank you.
Good, okay.

33:24.393 --> 33:26.004
Okay.

33:29.311 --> 33:32.097
- I, uh...

33:32.140 --> 33:34.838
I did break in.

33:34.882 --> 33:36.362
And I'm real sorry about that.

33:38.494 --> 33:39.887
- Tell her why.

33:43.064 --> 33:45.632
- I, uh...

33:45.675 --> 33:47.155
I...

33:47.199 --> 33:50.680
I just lost my mom.

33:50.724 --> 33:53.422
And, uh...

33:53.466 --> 33:54.771
it was sudden.

33:54.815 --> 33:58.166
And ...didn't know

33:58.210 --> 34:02.040
what to do,
where to go, but...

34:02.083 --> 34:05.826
your place--
your place, it felt safe.

34:05.869 --> 34:09.699
Felt familiar.

34:09.743 --> 34:12.093
Like home.

34:14.704 --> 34:17.011
- I'm sorry about your mom.

34:17.055 --> 34:19.970
I know how hard that must be.

34:20.014 --> 34:21.668
- I just really miss her.

34:24.192 --> 34:25.585
- What was she like?

34:30.329 --> 34:31.591
- I know.

34:32.896 --> 34:35.464
Go on.
Tell her.

34:38.467 --> 34:44.952
<i>♪</i>

34:48.173 --> 34:51.001
- She was...

34:51.045 --> 34:53.395
one of a kind.

34:54.483 --> 34:56.224
She was funny

34:56.268 --> 35:00.446
and smart and honest.

35:04.014 --> 35:05.755
- I lost my son, you know.

35:05.799 --> 35:12.675
<i>♪</i>

35:19.987 --> 35:21.945
- You on the list?

35:21.989 --> 35:23.643
- Am I what?

35:23.686 --> 35:25.949
- You on the list?

35:25.993 --> 35:27.995
- It's cool.
He's with me.

35:29.214 --> 35:31.085
- I'm with her.

35:31.129 --> 35:33.740
I just came by to check
on Brunstetter.

35:33.783 --> 35:37.047
- No ocular damage,
and the bone is stabilized.

35:37.091 --> 35:40.225
He's gonna be okay.
- Good, great.

35:40.268 --> 35:45.882
And what can you tell me
about them?

35:45.926 --> 35:48.146
- We defunded the police.
- What?

35:48.189 --> 35:49.799
While I was in Connecticut?

35:49.843 --> 35:51.236
- All these bouncers,

35:51.279 --> 35:53.281
who know a thing or two
about de-escalation,

35:53.325 --> 35:55.327
were out of work
thanks to COVID.

35:55.370 --> 35:57.981
Now they have a job
that comes with healthcare.

35:58.025 --> 35:59.679
- Is this gentleman
bothering you?

35:59.722 --> 36:01.420
- I was just leaving.

36:04.553 --> 36:11.473
<i>♪</i>

36:18.828 --> 36:19.916
- Seriously?

36:19.960 --> 36:21.135
- I heard about your day.

36:21.179 --> 36:23.050
And I came to apologize.

36:23.093 --> 36:24.443
Epic fail on my part,

36:24.486 --> 36:27.054
but then I pictured Cassian

36:27.097 --> 36:29.491
not even knowing who you were.

36:29.535 --> 36:32.015
Sorry, sorry.

36:32.059 --> 36:33.234
- Thanks.

36:33.278 --> 36:34.888
- It's kind of funny.

36:34.931 --> 36:37.282
Right?
Sorry.

36:37.325 --> 36:38.326
- What did--
this is, like,

36:38.370 --> 36:40.198
the worst apology ever.
- I know.

36:40.241 --> 36:43.026
Sorry, again.
I just, um...

36:43.070 --> 36:44.854
I had kind of a day myself.

36:44.898 --> 36:48.249
I got nothing left in the tank.

36:48.293 --> 36:51.209
-
You got nothing left.

36:51.252 --> 36:54.690
I'm living out of my suitcase,
with my mom,

36:54.734 --> 36:57.084
my marriage was over
before it ever began,

36:57.127 --> 37:01.523
and the one place
that I ever felt right

37:01.567 --> 37:03.612
doesn't have a place for me.

37:05.832 --> 37:07.747
- I know lots of places that
would happily give you

37:07.790 --> 37:09.052
their cardio department.

37:09.096 --> 37:11.881
- I don't care
about other places, man.

37:11.925 --> 37:13.492
I care about here.

37:13.535 --> 37:16.886
Look, you wanna stick me in the
classroom, teaching interns,

37:16.930 --> 37:18.540
I'm there.

37:18.584 --> 37:20.629
You want me to assist
in general surgeries,

37:20.673 --> 37:21.630
I'll take it.

37:21.674 --> 37:23.589
- That's a huge step down
for you.

37:23.632 --> 37:26.505
- Huge step down from what?
I'm already there.

37:28.507 --> 37:32.293
What I need is a hand
getting back up.

37:35.340 --> 37:42.434
<i>♪</i>

37:52.966 --> 37:59.886
- In Korea, women in mourning
wear white bows in their hair.

37:59.929 --> 38:01.714
This is the best I could do
in K-town.

38:03.237 --> 38:04.543
- May I?

38:04.586 --> 38:06.632
- Yeah.

38:06.675 --> 38:13.595
<i>♪</i>

38:23.170 --> 38:25.607
- We had the same father.

38:25.651 --> 38:28.480
<i>- ♪ Don't let your mind
get weary ♪</i>

38:28.523 --> 38:30.351
He was younger than me.

38:31.874 --> 38:35.269
I didn't even know that he
existed till six years ago.

38:37.358 --> 38:39.491
I only met him once.

38:41.493 --> 38:43.016
But once was all it took.

38:43.059 --> 38:45.888
<i>- ♪ Don't let your heart get
heavy ♪</i>

38:45.932 --> 38:49.327
- I knew he was my brother.

38:49.370 --> 38:51.198
Without a doubt.

38:57.117 --> 39:00.990
Is this what your family does
when someone dies?

39:01.034 --> 39:02.949
- Martha and Tim Shinnler?

39:02.992 --> 39:04.777
No, they wouldn't know
a Korean mourning custom

39:04.820 --> 39:07.736
from a hole in the ground.
- Wait, Shinnler?

39:09.782 --> 39:12.175
- I was adopted.

39:12.219 --> 39:14.482
When I was three.

39:14.526 --> 39:16.876
I shortened my name right
after college.

39:16.919 --> 39:18.486
As far as the hairclip,
I learned about that

39:18.530 --> 39:20.314
in my Korean lit class.

39:20.358 --> 39:22.360
- Huh.

39:22.403 --> 39:24.187
So your family's...

39:24.231 --> 39:27.321
- German Irish.

39:27.365 --> 39:29.584
I actually had to teach myself
to be Korean.

39:31.412 --> 39:32.848
Still really don't know how.

39:32.892 --> 39:37.853
<i>- ♪ In you,
that's where you'll find ♪</i>

39:37.897 --> 39:42.989
- So what else did you learn in
these college classes of yours?

39:45.339 --> 39:52.346
<i>♪</i>

40:03.270 --> 40:05.925
- Leyla, we should talk.

40:07.492 --> 40:11.931
- I knew using your showers
was too good to last.

40:11.974 --> 40:14.934
Well, get it over with.

40:17.676 --> 40:20.853
- Grab your stuff.
It's not safe out here.

40:35.128 --> 40:37.478
This is my secret spot.

40:42.265 --> 40:43.702
- Why do this for me?

40:45.443 --> 40:46.922
- I protect my people.

40:55.496 --> 40:57.498
- Here we go, you ready?

40:57.542 --> 41:00.153
- Yeah.
- Here it is.

41:00.196 --> 41:02.285
This is home.

41:02.329 --> 41:03.939
You remember this place?

41:03.983 --> 41:05.375
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

41:05.419 --> 41:07.508
There's a couch over there,
right?

41:07.552 --> 41:10.119
This is our kitchen.
Remember the kitchen?

41:10.163 --> 41:11.599
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

41:11.643 --> 41:15.603
This is where you're gonna
throw lots of food at Dada

41:15.647 --> 41:17.126
until he figures out
what you want,

41:17.170 --> 41:19.215
which I guess is not peas
anymore.

41:19.259 --> 41:22.305
And this is our sleepy room.

41:22.349 --> 41:24.220
This is my bed.

41:24.264 --> 41:28.050
And this,
this bed is for you.

41:28.094 --> 41:29.791
You like it?

41:29.835 --> 41:31.271
- Yeah.

41:35.841 --> 41:40.976
And this place...

41:41.020 --> 41:43.022
this is just for you.

41:43.065 --> 41:46.025
I know it's not much,

41:46.068 --> 41:48.027
but, uh...

41:49.855 --> 41:52.161
- Dada here.

41:52.205 --> 41:54.773
<i>♪</i>

41:54.816 --> 41:55.730
- Yeah.

42:00.474 --> 42:02.520
Yeah, Dada here.

42:13.052 --> 42:16.142
Dada's always here.

42:16.185 --> 42:18.405
- Yeah.
- Yeah.
